    "recap_headline": "North Carolina State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "TALLAHASSEE, Fla. \u2013\nNo. 10 NC State lost to No. 11 Florida State 15-5 in the series finale Sunday afternoon at Mike Martin Field at Dick Howser Stadium. It was the Wolfpack's first run-rule loss of the season.\nThe Seminoles (19-4, 5-1) scored seven runs in the first two innings and scored in every inning but one to secure the 10-run victory.\nHeath Andrews\n(2-1) started for the Wolfpack (18-6, 3-3), allowing six runs on six hits with one walk and one strikeout in 1.2 innings.\nLuke Nixon\ndrove in the first runs for the Pack with his seventh hit of the series, a two-run double down the right field line to make it 8-2. It was his team's eighth double of the season.\nCooper Consiglio\nrelieved Andrews, pitching a scoreless fourth inning, but the Seminoles responded in the fifth with three runs. He finished after three innings, giving up three earned runs on four hits with three walks and three strikeouts.\nRyder Garino\nand\nAiden Kitchings\nalso pitched out of the bullpen.\nIn the top of the seventh, NC State loaded the bases with nobody out.\nChris McHugh\nsingled in two runs, and\nDalton Bargo\nhad a sacrifice fly to cut the lead to three runs, but the deficit was too large, and the Seminoles held on to win.\nThe Wolfpack will return to Doak Field on Tuesday, March 24th, for a midweek game against in-state rival Campbell at 6 p.m.",
